omg, Heather and Angie stayed until 1:30 am to meet The Strokes. I am so pissed.....I bet they hardly even like them, they probably just thought it was cool or trendy. Ok, time to tell you about the show!

We arrived at the Norva around 6:15 pm and doors were scheduled to open at 7. It was bitterly cold outside and raining which made it a little unpleasant. I looked at the door posters and it said the show was sold out and I was like......ok, it wasn't last time I checked which had been pretty recent. Anyways, Braden couldn't go with us so we found a scalper who bought her ticket for $30. We were one of the first people in line and we would have had first row but 10 minutes before they let us all in they told everyone that was 21 or over they could go ahead and come in if they want, so I got screwed over. At the beginning of the gig, I was in the 4th row, and I think I ended up in like the 6th or 7th.....! My dad went up to the balcony and left me and Sam by ourselves. I had to listen to these middle aged people talk about The White Stripes being the greatest band.....they better have been fucking joking. Ok, so The Sounds come out and the girl (I forget her name) is so cute and everything. They are really good and the keyboardist was super attractive. After the Sounds, we wait for a while and my sister and I strike up a conversation with this cool half drunk blonde lady behind us who thought I was 20 or 21 and even her sober friends thought the same. By this time, my feet are killing me because I decided to be a dumbass like last show and wear heels. The Strokes come out and umm, they fucking rocked. Julian was super hott and I got plenty of pictures of him. He dove into the audience and I ALMOST touched him. It's a good thing he wasn't right on top of me because I would have unclothed the man. They played The Clash's "Clampdown" and it was really good. He asked us if 96x was a good station and we said, "HELL NO, IT SUCKS!" During the last song of the night "Last Night", he climbed onto the speakers and climbed onto the left side of the balcony section and started kissing people and going insane....it was great. Oh yeah, and Fab needs a bit of a haircut, and they are all super awesome.
